    <discussion>A closely related Eurasian diploid species, Chenopodium hybridum Linnaeus, probably
        also occurs in North America as introduced. Its occurrence in the New World needs
        confirmation. Chenopodium simplex differs from its Eurasian counterpart in having a smoother
        seed coat, a yellowish pericarp that is more adherent to the seed, and a different
        chromosome number (A. I. Baranov 1964; R. D. Dorn 1988b).</discussion>
